y\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#chapter-15--ensuring-telemetry-integrity\" aria-label=\"chapter 15  ensuring telemetry integrity permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><strong>Chapter 15 ‚Äî Ensuring Telemetry Integrity</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Making telemetry <strong>tamper-resistant</strong> and auditable.</li>\n<li>Write-only emission methods, access logging, and secure queues .</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"chapter-16--redacting-and-reprocessing-telemetry\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#chapter-16--redacting-and-reprocessing-telemetry\" aria-label=\"chapter 16  redacting and reprocessing telemetry permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><strong>Chapter 16 ‚Äî Redacting and Reprocessing Telemetry</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Handling <strong>toxic data</strong> (PII, GDPR).</li>\n<li>Real-time and batch redaction pipelines.</li>\n<li>Re-ingestion for platform migrations.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"chapter-17--building-policies-for-retention-and-aggregation\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a h